schms-entity-mutation-parity — complete the entity mutation subset needed by SCHMS regression tests
====================================================================================================

Context
-------

SCHMS is preparing one portable batch regression corpus to run unchanged under
AutoCAD, BricsCAD and clautolisp.  Its first tranche deliberately excludes UI
and rendering.  It creates, reads, modifies and deletes drawing entities, then
compares a normalized snapshot of the resulting drawing state.

The parent `drawing-database-api.issue` defines the long-term drawing value and
public Common Lisp API.  This issue is the narrower compatibility milestone
needed to run the first SCHMS corpus against the current in-memory mock host.
It does not replace that parent issue.

Required subset
---------------

Audit against AutoCAD and BricsCAD, then implement or correct:

  - ENTMAKE and ENTMAKEX for the graphical and non-graphical entity kinds used
    by the selected SCHMS corpus;
  - ENTGET, including requested application XData;
  - ENTMOD with replacement/removal of ordinary DXF groups and XData;
  - ENTDEL deletion and documented restore semantics;
  - ENTNEXT, ENTlast and stable traversal of main and subentities;
  - block/attribute and polyline/subentity ownership relationships;
  - handle/ename validity before and after mutation.

`entmakex-returns-list.issue` is an already known defect and remains the
specific issue for ENTMAKEX's return value.

Tests
-----

Add tests at three levels where applicable:

  1. pure host/model unit tests;
  2. AutoLISP builtin tests;
  3. portable `.lsp` conformance scenarios also runnable in the CAD products.

Include at least one create -> read -> modify -> read -> delete scenario for
each entity family required by the initial SCHMS inventory.  Probe ambiguous
vendor behaviour rather than encoding a convenient mock-host behaviour.

Acceptance
----------

  - The agreed SCHMS entity-mutation inventory is recorded in this issue.
  - All selected scenarios run without engine-specific branches in their
    assertions.
  - Returned DXF data and error behaviour match the selected CAD dialect
    profile.
  - Deleted entities, subentities and ownership links have vendor-compatible
    visibility and validity.
  - Existing clautolisp tests remain green on SBCL and CCL.
  - Any deliberately deferred entity family has its own named issue and is
    reported as skipped, not silently accepted.

Out of scope
------------

Interactive selection, commands requiring a graphical session, rendering,
DWG persistence, and the full multi-document work from
`drawing-database-api.issue`.



================================================================
STATUS (schms-parity, clautolisp 1.6.5 / 1.6.6)
================================================================

Headless core: DONE. Vendor-probe verification: BLOCKED on real CAD.

The entity CRUD foundation is implemented end to end (drawing model +
mock-host adapter + AutoLISP builtins) and green across the SBCL suites
(drawing 223, autolisp-host 30, autolisp-mock-host 686,
autolisp-builtins-core 1453; alfe conformance clautolisp entity scenario
PASS, CAD scenarios SKIPPED). Left OPEN as the umbrella tracking issue
for the deferred families below and the CAD-blocked verification tail.

ENT* verb coverage
------------------

  - ENTMAKE   — validates against the family registry; returns the
                SUPPLIED list on success (vendor echo, no injected -1/5),
                nil + ERRNO 36 on failure; no CL condition leaks.
  - ENTMAKEX  — returns the new entity's ENAME (issue
                entmakex-returns-list, now CLOSED); non-graphical ok.
  - ENTGET    — + the (entget ename '("APP" ...)) application-xdata form;
                xdata suppressed without an applist, "*" = all.
  - ENTMOD    — replaces ordinary groups wholesale; edits xdata per
                application (replace / empty-removes / preserve-unlisted /
                no-(-3)-leaves-xdata-untouched).
  - ENTDEL    — delete + within-session restore toggle.
  - ENTNEXT / ENTLAST — stable creation-order traversal of main entities
                AND subentities.
  - HANDENT   — hex handle -> ename, incl. session-deleted entities.
  - ENTUPD    — ename on a live entity, nil on a deleted one.

Subentity ownership (group 330): a POLYLINE / INSERT opens a run; each
following VERTEX / ATTRIB / SEQEND gets its 330 owner set to the header
handle unless the caller supplied one; SEQEND closes the run. ENTNEXT
walks header -> subentities -> seqend.

Implemented + validated entity families (21)
--------------------------------------------

LINE POINT CIRCLE ARC ELLIPSE LWPOLYLINE POLYLINE VERTEX SEQEND SPLINE
TEXT MTEXT ATTDEF ATTRIB INSERT 3DFACE SOLID TRACE RAY XLINE   (graphical)
XRECORD                                                        (object)

Each carries its DXF-reference required-code set, the AcDbEntity/
AcDbObject + per-class (100) subclass markers, and a layer-"0" default.
Registry + validation: clautolisp/drawing/source/entity-families.lisp.

Known limitation on the registered families: only the REQUIRED codes are
validated and only layer + subclass markers are defaulted. The deeper
per-family optional-code defaulting the vendor applies (e.g. INSERT
41/42/43 scale = 1, TEXT 72/73 alignment, ELLIPSE/SPLINE count
consistency) is NOT yet enforced — it is exactly what the CAD probes are
meant to pin down, so it is held until real-CAD verification is possible.

Deferred families (each has its own issue)
------------------------------------------

Types outside the 21 above are accepted PERMISSIVELY by ENTMAKE/ENTMAKEX
(pass-through, no validation) so no client is blocked, and are tracked
for full modelling by:

  - entity-family-annotation.issue          DIMENSION, LEADER, MLEADER,
                                             TOLERANCE, MLINE, MTEXT-adv
  - entity-family-hatch-image-boundary.issue HATCH/MPOLYGON, WIPEOUT,
                                             IMAGE, OLE2FRAME
  - entity-family-3d-solids.issue            3DSOLID, REGION, BODY,
                                             SURFACE, MESH, POLYLINE-mesh,
                                             HELIX
  - entity-family-tables-viewport-misc.issue ACAD_TABLE, VIEWPORT, SHAPE,
                                             LIGHT, SUN, etc.
  - entity-family-nongraphical-objects.issue DICTIONARY, GROUP, LAYOUT,
                                             PLOTSETTINGS, MATERIAL,
                                             *STYLE objects, etc.

Related defect found during this pass:

  - ename-eq-identity.issue — two ENAMEs for the same entity are not EQ
    (vendor: they are). Cross-cutting; deferred.

Vendor-probe verification (BLOCKED)
-----------------------------------

autolisp-front-end/tests/scenarios/entities/ holds a portable
entity-lifecycle probe + three alfe scenarios. The :clautolisp-only one
runs green now; the :bricscad-only / :autocad-only ones self-skip until a
BricsCAD / AutoCAD host is reachable. Running them there is the
verification tail that closes this issue.
